@{b}About@{ub}
=====

What is GuiAmiTCP?

Well if you haven't guessed its a Graphical Front End for Amitcp.

 
Basically all you have to do is click on buttons to get all of your 
amitcp things working. You don't have to worry about remembering all 
those annoying commands.

The main Button Box was created using the demo version of Nucleus,
a top menu creator. All other windows I created myself using TritonRexx.

I know what your are thinking...ARGH AREXX.

But it is a very useful language. (Also the only one i know)


@{b}Requirements@{ub}
============

Sitting there thinking "WHAT DO I NEED TO RUN THIS LOVELY PROGRAM?"

Didn't think so! ;)

Well I am going to tell you anyway! :)

Well to start with, a copy of Amitcp would be nice. Also the Tritonrexx
libraries and a copy of my program.

Hardware -  You need an Amiga (enough said) and a hard drive.
            You might also consider an Internet connection! ;)

            I understand you also need KS3 for TritonRexx.

            I was told this and do not REALLY know what it is.
            You will just have to try it and see! 

@{"Return to main page " Link "Main"} @{" Installation " Link "Installation"}

@EndNode

