@{b}Installation@{ub}
============

How to install this THING! :) 

The Unpacked Archive will create a drawer call GuiAmiTCP


In this directory there SHOULD be the following files and directories.

Directories: 				Rexx
					

Files:				GuiAmiTCP.guide (In main dir)
  				GuiAmiTCP (In main dir)
                                
                All the .rexx files, in the Rexx directory. 
                
@{b}
     =============================================================
     |IMPORTANT: YOU NEED TO ASSIGN THE MAIN DIRECTORY TO GUITCP:|
     =============================================================
@{ub}
The Following Libraries are required in your LIBS: assign. 

The .library files are:
  
@{b}          tritonrexx.library
          rexxreqtools.library
          rexxsupport.library  @{ub}

THESE ARE IMPORTANT AS GUIAMITCP WILL NOT FUNCTION WITHOUT THEM!!!
                 
STARTNET: I suggest adding a line to your startnet such as:


@{b}run >nil: guitcp:GuiAmitcp@{ub}


This will load GuiAmiTCP whenever you Start your Amitcp SoftWare.

(Note that this is Optional. Also, be careful to close one Window before
 executing Startnet for second time, as you will end up with duplicate
 windows)

We now need to configure the program.....

@{"Return to About " Link "About"} @{" Configuration " Link "Configure"}

@EndNode

@Node "Configure"
@Next "Usage"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}Configuration@{ub}            
=======================

First of all, decide which window style you want. Rename the normal window
"GuiAmiTCPBOX" then rename your chosen window "GuiAmiTCP"

Load the program up by double clicking on the GuiAmiTCP icon.

Then pull down the Configuration menu (right mouse for all you newbies)
and open the "GuiAmiTCP Configuration" script.

A window will appear and you can enter all the details for your
EXTERNAL programs. These are the programs that are not part of Amitcp
but were written espescially for it.

I have left my own configuration as default, and as an example.

The configuration will create a file in your envarc: called

GuiAmiTCP.config

This file will look something like this:

amitcp:bin/mail
Dh2:WWW/Voyager/V
Dh2:Chat/Amirc/Amirc
Amitcp:bin/tin
Dh2:ftp/amftp/amftp
Amitcp:bin/Link Up
Amitcp:bin/Link Down

In the Config window the first text gadget will be your mailer. This is 
where you put the path and name of the mail program you use.

If you use amitcp's mail program then leave it as it is.

The second text gadget is the web browser you use. I use voyager, but you 
can put whatever you want in. 

    REMEMBER THAT YOU NEED TO SPECIFY THE PATH AND THE EXECUTABLE

The same goes for all the other text gadgets

"Link Up" and "Link down" 
========================

The last two gadgets...these are the programs you use to connect and 
disconnect from the internet. Users of Amitcp v3.0 (like me) will
have the commands "amitcp:bin/link" and then up or down.

Users of the Demon amitcp v4.2 demo will have the program "connect".

Just put the path and the executable command in the box and you will be
fine.

NOTE: IF YOU ARE TRYING TO RUN AN AREXX SCRIPT FROM GuiAmiTCP, YOU NEED
      TO PUT THE "RX" COMMAND IN FRONT. AS IF YOU WERE TYPING IT IN 
      MANUALLY.


@{"Return to Installation " Link "Installation"} @{" Usage " Link "Usage"}

@Endnode

